[
    {
        "text": "Hi. this is Danny Boyle,\nthe director of “Yesterday.”",
        "start": 0.51,
        "duration": 3.268
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’ve got a bunch\nof new songs.",
        "start": 3.778,
        "duration": 1.292
    },
    {
        "text": "And I thought people\nmight like to hear them.”",
        "start": 5.07,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "“Oh.”",
        "start": 6.67,
        "duration": 0.635
    },
    {
        "text": "So where we are\nin this scene is",
        "start": 7.305,
        "duration": 1.905
    },
    {
        "text": "that Jack has recovered from\nthe accident, which happened",
        "start": 9.21,
        "duration": 3.72
    },
    {
        "text": "during the blackout, where\nthe Beatles were erased",
        "start": 12.93,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": "from the world’s\nconsciousness.",
        "start": 15.75,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "And he’s discovered\nthe opportunity,",
        "start": 17.61,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "which is to revitalize his\nown fairly unsuccessful",
        "start": 20.89,
        "duration": 4.91
    },
    {
        "text": "singer-songwriting career by\nactually playing the Beatles",
        "start": 25.8,
        "duration": 3.3
    },
    {
        "text": "songs that he can remember.",
        "start": 29.1,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "“Right.",
        "start": 30.94,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "This is called “Let It Be.’”",
        "start": 31.44,
        "duration": 4.66
    },
    {
        "text": "So Himesh Patel\nplays Jack Malik.",
        "start": 36.1,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s his mom, Meera Syal\nand Sanjeev Bhaskar, who are,",
        "start": 38.25,
        "duration": 3.45
    },
    {
        "text": "in fact, a real life couple.",
        "start": 41.7,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "But actually, they are\nalso two of the finest",
        "start": 43.74,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "comic actors in\nBritain, as well,",
        "start": 45.93,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "independently of each other.",
        "start": 47.76,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "And he starts to sing\nby saying to his parents",
        "start": 49.19,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "that he’s got a couple of new\nsongs he wants to try out,",
        "start": 51.19,
        "duration": 3.32
    },
    {
        "text": "and he’s going to go\nback to performing,",
        "start": 54.51,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "even though they thought\nhe was giving up.",
        "start": 56.19,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "They wanted him to give\nup, because they think",
        "start": 57.94,
        "duration": 2.488
    },
    {
        "text": "it’s a bit of a dead end.",
        "start": 60.428,
        "duration": 1.042
    },
    {
        "text": "[music - “let it be’]",
        "start": 61.47,
        "duration": 0.679
    },
    {
        "text": "“(SINGING) comes to me — “",
        "start": 62.149,
        "duration": 1.082
    },
    {
        "text": "[doorbell ringing]",
        "start": 63.231,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": "“ — speaking — “",
        "start": 63.981,
        "duration": 0.582
    },
    {
        "text": "“Oh, oh.",
        "start": 64.563,
        "duration": 0.566
    },
    {
        "text": "Sorry, love.”",
        "start": 65.129,
        "duration": 1.351
    },
    {
        "text": "They’re inclined to think\nthis is Jack just indulging",
        "start": 66.48,
        "duration": 3.3
    },
    {
        "text": "the dead end of his career.",
        "start": 69.78,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "So they don’t sense\nthat they are actually",
        "start": 71.74,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "the first people on\nEarth to apparently hear",
        "start": 75.18,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "one of the greatest\nmasterpieces of pop",
        "start": 78.42,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "music ever written.",
        "start": 80.64,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "“Really?",
        "start": 81.96,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "I thought — I thought\nhe’d given up?”",
        "start": 82.46,
        "duration": 1.105
    },
    {
        "text": "“Yeah.",
        "start": 83.565,
        "duration": 0.085
    },
    {
        "text": "No.",
        "start": 83.65,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, he’s got some new songs.",
        "start": 84.15,
        "duration": 1.57
    },
    {
        "text": "And what’s this one called?”",
        "start": 85.72,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "“’Leave It Be.’”",
        "start": 87.15,
        "duration": 1.037
    },
    {
        "text": "“’Let It Be.’”",
        "start": 88.187,
        "duration": 0.583
    },
    {
        "text": "“Oh, excellent, well — “",
        "start": 88.77,
        "duration": 0.958
    },
    {
        "text": "The misnaming of the\nsong was something",
        "start": 89.728,
        "duration": 2.552
    },
    {
        "text": "that Meera Syal came\nup with on the day.",
        "start": 92.28,
        "duration": 1.735
    },
    {
        "text": "[music - “let it be’]",
        "start": 94.015,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": "“(SINGING) When I find\nmyself in times of trouble — “",
        "start": 94.89,
        "duration": 3.252
    },
    {
        "text": "“Would you like\na drink, Terry?”",
        "start": 98.142,
        "duration": 1.333
    },
    {
        "text": "“(SPEAKING) Dad!”",
        "start": 99.475,
        "duration": 0.785
    },
    {
        "text": "“Well, I’d already\nheard that bit.”",
        "start": 100.26,
        "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
        "text": "“Sorry, Jack.”",
        "start": 101.93,
        "duration": 1.322
    },
    {
        "text": "Everything that can\ninterrupt the song",
        "start": 103.252,
        "duration": 1.718
    },
    {
        "text": "is essential to the comedy\nof the scene, really.",
        "start": 104.97,
        "duration": 3.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Because as Jack fights\nfor the great masterpiece",
        "start": 108.61,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "of cultural achievement\nto be heard,",
        "start": 112.05,
        "duration": 2.338
    },
    {
        "text": "it’s not even\nallowed any room.",
        "start": 114.388,
        "duration": 1.292
    },
    {
        "text": "Because everybody’s too\nbusy with their phones,",
        "start": 115.68,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "with their beer.",
        "start": 117.87,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "And Karl Theobald,\nwho plays Terry,",
        "start": 119.01,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "does a wonderful\ntapping of the sofa arm,",
        "start": 121.05,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": "out of time to the song,\nwhich is the ultimate insult.",
        "start": 123.87,
        "duration": 3.88
    },
    {
        "text": "[cellphone ringing]",
        "start": 127.75,
        "duration": 0.792
    },
    {
        "text": "“Sorry, my fault. Oh.”",
        "start": 128.542,
        "duration": 3.563
    },
    {
        "text": "So the key thing was to try\nand find the living room that",
        "start": 132.105,
        "duration": 3.045
    },
    {
        "text": "looked incredibly ordinary.",
        "start": 135.15,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "We wanted it to feel\nvery, very ordinary.",
        "start": 137.73,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": "And I remember on\nthe day turning up",
        "start": 139.87,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "that we kept the property\nlooking almost the same as it",
        "start": 141.51,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "was when we found it.",
        "start": 144.09,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "Because it looked perfect.",
        "start": 147.48,
        "duration": 1.23
    },
    {
        "text": "But they didn’t have a piano.",
        "start": 148.71,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "So then they brought along on\nthe day, a choice of pianos.",
        "start": 150.42,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "And we — this piano\nthat he plays on",
        "start": 153.81,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "is not the best tuned piano.",
        "start": 155.82,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "But I wanted it to look like\nit was the piano that he",
        "start": 158.79,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "grew up learning on.",
        "start": 161.43,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "The ordinary is very\nimportant in the film.",
        "start": 164.1,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "Because where the\nguys came from,",
        "start": 167.04,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "the Fab Four, the\noriginal Beatles,",
        "start": 169.47,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "was from a very\nordinary town, in a way.",
        "start": 171.72,
        "duration": 2.025
    },
    {
        "text": "[music - “let it be’]",
        "start": 173.745,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": "“Then maybe we can\nhave summer songs!”",
        "start": 174.62,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "[dissonant banging on piano]",
        "start": 176.08,
        "duration": 0.738
    },
    {
        "text": "“Christ!",
        "start": 176.818,
        "duration": 0.738
    },
    {
        "text": "This is “Let It Be!”",
        "start": 177.556,
        "duration": 1.724
    },
    {
        "text": "You’re the first people on\nEarth to hear this song!”",
        "start": 179.28,
        "duration": 3.57
    },
    {
        "text": "So many of us have\ntried to persuade",
        "start": 182.85,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "our parents to listen\nto a song, you know,",
        "start": 184.35,
        "duration": 2.028
    },
    {
        "text": "because we love it.",
        "start": 186.378,
        "duration": 0.792
    },
    {
        "text": "And they can’t hear it.",
        "start": 187.17,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "We all know that\nscenario, don’t we?",
        "start": 188.31,
        "duration": 2.642
    },
    {
        "text": "One of the reasons we\npicked the location",
        "start": 190.952,
        "duration": 1.708
    },
    {
        "text": "is that it’s got this\nround glass, which",
        "start": 192.66,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "gives a distorted view\nof people arriving.",
        "start": 194.85,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "They’re kind of,\nlike, out of focus.",
        "start": 197.26,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "They’re grotesque, really.",
        "start": 199.67,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Which is what they\nfeel like to him.",
        "start": 200.99,
        "duration": 1.952
    },
    {
        "text": "“How are you?”",
        "start": 202.942,
        "duration": 0.81
    },
    {
        "text": "“Fine.”",
        "start": 203.752,
        "duration": 0.743
    },
    {
        "text": "“Well, that went well.”",
        "start": 204.495,
        "duration": 2.015
    }
]